summary: Extra Space Storage (EXR) delivered FFO and revenue surprises of +0.97% and -0.73%, respectively, for the quarter ended September 2025. Do the numbers hold clues to what lies ahead for the stock?

headline: Extra Space Storage: Q3 Earnings Snapshot
summary: The Salt Lake City-based real estate investment trust said it had funds from operations of $461.1 million, or $2.08 per share, in the period. The average estimate of eight analysts surveyed by Zacks Investment Research was for funds from operations of $2.06 per share. Funds from operations is a closely watched measure in the REIT industry.

headline: Extra Space Storage Inc. Reports 2025 Third Quarter Results
summary: Extra Space Storage Inc. (NYSE: EXR) (the "Company"), a leading owner and operator of self-storage facilities in the United States and a constituent of the S&P 500 index, announced operating results for the three and nine months ended September 30, 2025.
